headline: Inspire Medical Stock Is Down 38% This Year. Why It’s Surging Today.
summary: A small medical device maker caused a stir on Wall Street as its shares surged by double digits.  The steep gains came after  Stifel  analyst Jonathan Block upgraded the stock to Buy from Hold and lifted his price target to $110 from $100.  Block cited a “large positive reimbursement revision” the company received Friday evening, when the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services issued its annual update.
